channel.title: Compile errors - NOT JAVAC ERROR!
channel.description:
I KNOW WHAT YOURE THINKING! its not the javac error lol. so i tried to compile and this is what i get:
[code]client.java:2676: illegal start of type if (command.startsWith("cw")) { ^ client.java:3326: <identifier> expected ^ client.java:3332: 'class' or 'interface' expected public void fromBank(int itemID, int fromSlot, int amount) { ^ client.java:5714: 'class' or 'interface' expected public int packetSize = 0, packetType = -1; ^ client.java:5715: 'class' or 'interface' expected public boolean process() { // is being called regularily ev ery 500ms ^ client.java:10684: 'class' or 'interface' expected public boolean ResetPlayerVars() { ^ client.java:10898: 'class' or 'interface' expected public int EssenceMineY[] = {4846,4846,4832,4817,4817}; ^ client.java:10906: 'class' or 'interface' expected public int EssenceMineRX[] = {3253,3105,2681,2591}; ^ client.java:10907: 'class' or 'interface' expected public int EssenceMineRY[] = {3401,9571,3325,3086}; ^ client.java:10914: 'class' or 'interface' expected public boolean stairs(int stairs, int teleX, int teleY) { ^ client.java:13736: 'class' or 'interface' expected public int Publicchat = 0; ^ client.java:13738: 'class' or 'interface' expected public void pmstatus(int status) { //status: loading = 0 connecting = 1 fine = 2 ^ client.java:17686: 'class' or 'interface' expected } ^ client.java:17687: 'class' or 'interface' expected ^ 14 errors Press any key to continue . . .[/code]

item.title: Compile errors - NOT JAVAC ERROR!
item.dc:creator: @Unseen Unseen
item.description:
@Unseen wrote:

I HIGHLY suggest you always keep backups of your server. Make a folder called “Server Backup” and after every single successfull compilation copy your whole server folder into that one (and overwrite every time so you keep your newest edit). That way you don’t lose 2 months of great work over 1 edit, you only have to fix that edit.
